wikipedia_page.main: Sabrina Fortune (born 25 May 1997) is a British Paralympic track and field athlete from Wales competing in category F20 throwing events. Fortune won a bronze medal at the 2016 Summer Paralympics in the shot put and a gold medal at the 2019 World Para Athletics Championships, also in shot put.
